docs.abstract: Residents rarely learn how data centers and their noise and energy and water use may affect their lives until it’s too late.
docs.snippet: Residents rarely learn how data centers and their noise and energy and water use may affect their lives until it’s too late.
docs.lead_paragraph: The revolution in artificial intelligence that promised us breakthroughs in medical research and corporate productivity seems to be running a little behind. But already A.I. has become something of a nightmare for the Americans who happen to live near one of the more than 5,000 data centers that power it and keep the cloud above our digital world running.

headline.main: Noisy, Hungry Data Centers Are Catching Communities by Surprise

docs.abstract: Sam Altman, OpenAI’s chief executive, is talking to the United Arab Emirates, Asian chipmakers and U.S. officials to expand the computing power needed to build artificial intelligence.
docs.snippet: Sam Altman, OpenAI’s chief executive, is talking to the United Arab Emirates, Asian chipmakers and U.S. officials to expand the computing power needed to build artificial intelligence.
docs.lead_paragraph: Late last year, Sam Altman, the chief executive of OpenAI, started pitching an audacious plan that he hoped would create the computing power his company needed to build more powerful artificial intelligence.

headline.main: Behind OpenAI’s Audacious Plan to Make A.I. Flow Like Electricity
headline.print_headline: Behind OpenAI’s Audacious Plan  To Make A.I. Flow Like Electricity

byline.original: By Cade Metz and Tripp Mickle

docs.abstract: As the company looks for more outside investors, documents reviewed by The New York Times show consumer fascination with ChatGPT and a serious need for more cash.
docs.snippet: As the company looks for more outside investors, documents reviewed by The New York Times show consumer fascination with ChatGPT and a serious need for more cash.
docs.lead_paragraph: OpenAI, the San Francisco start-up behind ChatGPT, has been telling investors that it is making billions from its chatbot and that it expects to make a lot more in the coming years. But it has not been quite so clear about how much it is losing.

headline.main: OpenAI Is Growing Fast and Burning Through Piles of Money
headline.print_headline: High Cost Of Growth For OpenAI

byline.original: By Mike Isaac and Erin Griffith

docs.abstract: The indictment unsealed on Thursday comes as the United States expands its hunt for Russia’s most elite cyberwarriors.
docs.snippet: The indictment unsealed on Thursday comes as the United States expands its hunt for Russia’s most elite cyberwarriors.
docs.lead_paragraph: The United States expanded its hunt on Thursday for Russia’s most elite cyberwarriors, indicting five members of the country’s military intelligence agency for attacks on Ukraine and American companies in the run-up to the invasion of Ukraine in 2022.

headline.main: U.S. Indicts Members of Russian Military Intelligence Over Cyberattack on Ukraine

byline.original: By David E. Sanger and Julian E. Barnes
